Package com.atakmap.map.layer.raster.tilematrix.opengl

Class GLTile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.atakmap.map.layer.raster.tilematrix.opengl.GLTile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GLMapBatchable2, GLMapRenderable2, GLResolvable, Releasable
    public class GLTile
extends java.lang.Object
implements GLMapRenderable2, GLMapBatchable2, GLResolvable
    Renderer for a single tile for a Tiled Map Layer. The tile renderer is responsible for requesting the loading of the tile, uploading the tile data to a texture, managing the lifetime of the tile texture and rendering the tile data to the screen during the draw pump.

      • draw

        public void draw​(GLMapView view,
                 int renderPass)
        Description copied from interface: GLMapRenderable2
        Renders the content in the current EGL context for the given view. Initialization of the renderer may occur following instantiation or a prior call to GLMapRenderable2.release().

        This method is ALWAYS invoked on the GL thread.

        Specified by:
        draw in interface GLMapRenderable2
        Parameters:
        view - The current view
        renderPass - The render pass being executed during this invocation. The value will be the bitwise-OR of any of the flags:
        • GLMapView.RENDER_PASS_SURFACE
        • GLMapView.RENDER_PASS_SPRITES
        Only content valid for the specified pass should be rendered.

      • release

        public void release()
        Description copied from interface: GLMapRenderable2
        Releases any resources allocated by the renderable as a result of the invocation of the #draw(GLMapView) method. This method will be invoked when a renderable that was previously being rendered is no longer eligible for rendering (e.g. a tile that is no longer in view on the map). The renderable may be reinitialized and rendered via a subsequent call to #draw(GLMapView) in the future.

        This method is ALWAYS invoked on the GL thread.

        Specified by:
        release in interface GLMapBatchable2
        Specified by:
        release in interface GLMapRenderable2
        Specified by:
        release in interface Releasable

      • suspend

        public void suspend()
        Description copied from interface: GLResolvable
        Resolution is suspended. If #draw(GLMapView) is invoked, any data that has already been loaded should be rendered, however, no new data should be loaded. The rest of the data may continue loading if GLResolvable.resume() is invoked.

        This method does nothing if the current state is not GLResolvable.State.RESOLVING.

        Specified by:
        suspend in interface GLResolvable

      • resume

        public void resume()
        Description copied from interface: GLResolvable
        Resolution is resumed. This method may be invoked following a call to GLResolvable.suspend() to resume loading data.

        This method does nothing if the current state is not GLResolvable.State.SUSPENDED.

        Specified by:
        resume in interface GLResolvable
